Subject: [PATCH 018/327] efi: Allow efi=runtime
Origin: https://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/projects/rt/4.19/older/patches-4.19.120-rt52.tar.xz

In case the option "efi=noruntime" is default at built-time, the user
could overwrite its sate by `efi=runtime' and allow it again.

Acked-by: Ard Biesheuvel <ard.biesheuvel@linaro.org>
Signed-off-by: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
---
 drivers/firmware/efi/efi.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/firmware/efi/efi.c b/drivers/firmware/efi/efi.c
index f1e0a2715269..3d5cbd3eedb4 100644
--- a/drivers/firmware/efi/efi.c
+++ b/drivers/firmware/efi/efi.c
@@ -113,6 +113,9 @@ static int __init parse_efi_cmdline(char *str)
 	if (parse_option_str(str, "noruntime"))
 		disable_runtime = true;
 
+	if (parse_option_str(str, "runtime"))
+		disable_runtime = false;
+
 	return 0;
 }
 early_param("efi", parse_efi_cmdline);
